      "deeperQuestionText": "Why is a complete loop back to the transformer necessary for safety, rather than just connecting a wire to the ground?",
      "deeperAnswerGuidance": [
        "Electricity requires a continuous path to flow",
        "Current must return to its source to complete the circuit",
        "A return path ensures enough current flows to trip protective devices",
        "The ground alone may not provide a low enough resistance path"
      ],
      "deeperSourceTeachingPointIds": [
        "TP1",
        "TP3",
        "TP4"
      ],
      "hint": "Consider what is required for a circuit breaker to detect a fault and disconnect the power."
    },
    {
      "title": "Internal vs. External Impedance",
