    "objective": "Synthesize the individual components (R1, R2, Ze, MET) into a complete description of the earth fault loop (Zs).",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "Scenario: A fault occurs between the line conductor and the metal casing of an electric heater.",
      "The circuit breaker must trip to ensure safety."
    ],
    "questionText": "Explain the complete journey the fault current takes from the point of the fault back to the supply transformer, identifying the specific internal and external components that make up the total earth fault loop impedance (Zs).",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Current travels from the fault through the circuit protective conductor (R2).",
      "The path continues through the Main Earthing Terminal (MET).",
      "Current flows back to the source via the Supplier Earth Return Path.",
      "The external part of the path (transformer and supply cables) is Ze.",
      "The loop is completed through the circuit line conductor (R1).",
      "The total resistance of this entire combined path is Zs."
    ],
    "hint": "Think about the 'loop'—start at the heater, go through the earth wiring, out of the building, through the transformer, and back to the heater via the live wire."
  }
}

